START A CLUB - CHECKLIST

INTRODUCTION
Starting a ruck club is a rewarding way to build community, improve fitness, and share the benefits of rucking with others. This guide provides practical steps to launch your own successful ruck club.

LEADERSHIP PRINCIPLES
☐ Vision: Clearly define what you want to achieve with your club.
☐ Planning: Develop a structured approach to launching and growing.
☐ Communication: Keep members informed and engaged.
☐ Adaptability: Be ready to adjust based on feedback and circumstances.
☐ Service: Focus on providing value to your members.

PRACTICAL CHECKLIST
☐ Research local interest and potential meeting locations.
☐ Define your club's purpose, values, and target audience.
☐ Set up a simple communication system (social media group, email list).
☐ Plan your first ruck event with a beginner-friendly route.
☐ Establish basic safety guidelines and equipment recommendations.
☐ Promote your launch through local networks and social media.
☐ Host your first ruck and gather feedback for improvement.
☐ Establish a regular meeting schedule based on member availability.
☐ Continuously evaluate and improve the club experience.